# Production Ollama model for birr-track receipt extraction.
#
# PHASE 2 OUTCOME (2026-05-29):
#
# Goal was to convert the fine-tuned LoRA → GGUF and serve via Ollama.
# Two paths were attempted:
#
#   1. Merge LoRA into Qwen2.5-VL-3B base → convert text+mmproj to GGUF →
#      quantize → load with two FROM directives.
#      Result: text generation works. Image grounding produces garbled
#      output. llama.cpp's Qwen2.5-VL mmproj conversion is unreliable in
#      the version we built against (verified by gibberish responses on
#      cbe_screenshot_1.jpg; stock 3B handles it correctly).
#
#   2. Convert LoRA adapter to GGUF and apply via Modelfile ADAPTER on top
#      of stock qwen2.5vl:3b.
#      Result: ollama errors with "loras are not yet implemented" for the
#      qwen25vl architecture.
#
# Until upstream tooling matures (llama.cpp mmproj conversion, or Ollama
# LoRA support for VL models), we ship the stock 3B model. It already
# produces correct JSON extraction on test receipts.
#
# The fine-tuning artifacts are preserved for future retry:
#   - vlm-inference/adapters/qwen25vl-3b-birrtrack-lora/  (HF PEFT adapter)
#   - qwen-vlm-training/merged/qwen25vl-3b-birrtrack/     (merged HF model)
#   - qwen-vlm-training/gguf/birrtrack-lora-f16.gguf      (LoRA as GGUF)
#   - qwen-vlm-training/gguf/birrtrack-qwen25vl-3b-text-q4_k_m.gguf
#   - qwen-vlm-training/gguf/birrtrack-qwen25vl-3b-mmproj-f16.gguf
#
# If the fine-tuned model is required *now*, set VLM_BACKEND=peft in
# vlm-inference/.env. PEFT runs the merged HF model directly via
# transformers — works on any device but slow on CPU.

FROM qwen2.5vl:3b

# Deterministic decoding for receipt extraction
PARAMETER temperature 0
PARAMETER top_p 1
PARAMETER num_predict 256
